# Frontend: Atomic Design Pattern

## Directory Structure

Always organise components under `app/src/components/` following the Atomic Design hierarchy:

```
src/
  components/
    atoms/        # Smallest building blocks (Button, Input, Badge, Icon, Label)
    molecules/    # Combinations of atoms (SearchBar, FormField, CardHeader)
    organisms/    # Complex UI sections (Navbar, Sidebar, DataTable, Modal)
    templates/    # Page-level layouts (DashboardLayout, AuthLayout)
  hooks/          # Custom React hooks
  lib/            # Utilities, API clients, constants
  store/          # State management (Zustand / React Context)
  types/          # Shared TypeScript types/interfaces
```

## Rules

### No Duplicate Components
- Before creating any component, search the entire `components/` tree.
- If a similar component exists, **extend it via props** — never copy-paste and rename.
- Shared logic must live in a custom hook inside `src/hooks/`, never duplicated inline.

### Component Authoring
- Every component must be a **named export** (not default export) for tree-shaking.
- Accept and forward `className` via `cn()` (use `clsx` + `tailwind-merge`) for style composition.
- Never hard-code colours or spacing that already exists in the Tailwind config.
- All props must have explicit TypeScript interfaces — no `any`.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD – atom
interface ButtonProps extends React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement> {
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'ghost';
  size?: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg';
  isLoading?: boolean;
}

export function Button({ variant = 'primary', size = 'md', isLoading, className, ...props }: ButtonProps) {
  return (
    <button
      className={cn(buttonVariants({ variant, size }), className)}
      disabled={isLoading || props.disabled}
      {...props}
    />
  );
}
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD – duplicating a Button just to change colour inline
export function RedButton(props) {
  return <button style={{ color: 'red' }} {...props} />;
}
```

### Placement Rules

| Level | Contains | Example |
|-------|----------|---------|
| Atom | Single HTML element or tiny wrapper | `Button`, `Input`, `Avatar`, `Spinner` |
| Molecule | 2–5 atoms with shared behaviour | `FormField`, `SearchInput`, `UserCard` |
| Organism | Multiple molecules, domain logic | `Header`, `DataTable`, `UserForm` |
| Template | Layout scaffolding, slot-based | `DashboardLayout`, `AuthLayout` |

### Hook Extraction
- Any stateful logic shared across ≥ 2 components must be extracted to `src/hooks/use<Name>.ts`.
- Hooks must return a typed object, never a positional tuple (except `useState`-style pairs).
